review.reviewText:
Disappointments: NO elevators, only stairs to rooms (all rooms on second and third floor); parking is limited as it is a "first come first serve" basis and the number of spots is less than rooms available; parking is only available if you have a compact car; free breakfast is a joke, exterior and interior are very outdated, with the exception of the bathroom, which had a little renovating; bed spreads had holes in them and there was an odor to the hotel in general.
Advantages: within walking distance to shopping, but not to Fisherman's Wharf;

Overall, we were disappointed with this hotel and do not believe the pictures or the free parking, free breakfast. Also, during our stay a car alarm went off and due to the cars being parked under the rooms and the openness of the motel, it was ridiculously loud.
